      "content": "You should absolutely not change your warfarin dosage without consulting your doctor, even if you feel great. Your current dose is precisely what your blood needs to stay in that safe, therapeutic range. Suddenly dropping to 2mg could put you at risk for clots, which is a serious medical event. Always follow the prescribed regimen and let your physician manage your anticoagulation levels.",
